linux commands and discription
man <command> -manual page of command
ls-     list files or directories
ls -l - long list of files
ls -lh - shows file sizes in a more human readable format
ls -a - list all files including hidden files
mkdir - make directory
rmdir -remove directory
cat   -show content of file
cd <directory>   -change directory
cd ~/ cd - return to home directory
cd .. - return to parent directory
pwd   -show present working directory
touch-create an empty file
cp <source file> <target file> -copy content of source file to the target file
mv <source file> <target file>-move content of source file to the target file
